This was a nice simple recipe if you're looking for a straight-forward cheesecake. However, I followed the cooking directions to a 'T', I even lengthened the cooking time by 15 minutes and it was still way underdone. Everyone raved about the flavor, but it was moosh in the middle. Some other reviewers did not seem to run into this problem, so I would recommend doing a test-run prior to a party or event. Otherwise, great, easy recipe.

Rating: 4
This is THE best cheesecake EVER! I always use 1 pint of plain (or vanilla) 0% fat greek yogurt instead of sour cream to lower the fat content and it tastes just as delicious. I also make the following variation to turn this into an Amaretto Cheesecake: 3 pkgs of cream cheese, 4 eggs, 1Tbsp almond extract, 1/4 cup Amaretto liqueur, 1 pint of vanilla greek yogurt (instead of the sour cream). Bake for 40 mins then turn off oven and leave it for 1 hr. Meanwhile mix 1/2 cup sliced almonds with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water. Dissolve water/sugar and drop in almonds. Stir. Remove with a slotted spoon onto wax paper and separate.. let cool while cheesecake is in the oven. After 1 hour, open door and arrange candied/praline almonds around the edge and return to oven and bake on 350 for about 10 mins more until almonds are brown. Remove from oven and cool. I've made this several times to rave reviews.

