Rating: 3
This recipe deserves credit because it seems pretty foolproof. I haven't had much luck with cheesecakes in the past, but this is the first recipe that suggested undercooking it and leaving it in the oven for an hour.. that must be the key. I live at a high altitude, cooked it for a generous 40 minutes and refrigerated it for 18 hrs. I think it could have used 5 more minutes in the oven; the center was a bit underdone, but quite edible and I'd rather have had it like that than overcooked. There was nary a crack. It turns out to be a rather flat cake. You can see from the recipe that it isn't any sort of fancy variation on cheesecake; it's very basic. It wasn't the cheesecake of my dreams, but it's dead easy and seems pretty foolproof, so I'm sure I'll be making it again.

